# Always Use Explicit Kube Context for Kind

When running kubectl, helm, or any k8s command targeting the local kind cluster,
ALWAYS use `--context kind-dex-e2e` (or the `KUBE_CONTEXT` env var).
NEVER rely on the default kube context — the user may have it set to a GKE
or other production cluster.

## Rules

- `kubectl --context kind-dex-e2e ...`
- `helm --kube-context kind-dex-e2e ...`
- Scripts: use `KUBE_CONTEXT="${KUBE_CONTEXT:-kind-dex-e2e}"` and pass it.
- NEVER run bare `kubectl` or `helm` without an explicit context.
